The '''Lower Excise Fuel and Beer Party''' is a minor [[Australia]]n political party that fielded several candidates in the [[Australian federal election, 2001|2001]] and [[Australian federal election, 2004|2004 Federal election]]s. Their main policies include repealing the [[Goods and Services Tax (Australia)|Goods and Services Tax]] and lowering the excise on fuel and beer prices. Many of their policies are centre-left. It was founded by David O'Loughlin, a [[Coffs Harbour, New South Wales|Coffs Harbour]] resident.
