ivan]], ''Cailleach: The Hag Of Beara''<ref>{{cite news|title=Cork poet O'Sullivan wins Rooney prize|url=http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/ireland/2010/1013/1224280972100.html|work=The Irish Times|date=10 October 2010}}</ref> * 2011: [[Lucy Caldwell]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Novelist and Dramatist Lucy Caldwell Awarded Rooney Prize 2011|url=http://www.tcd.ie/Communications/news/pressreleases/pressRelease.php?headerID=2116&vs_date=2011-10-26|publisher=Trinity College, Dublin|date=26 October 2011|accessdate=24 April 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120119073203/http://www.tcd.ie/Communications/news/pressreleases/pressRelease.php?headerID=2116&vs_date=2011-10-26|archivedate=19 January 2012|df=}}</ref> * 2012: [[Nancy Harris]]<ref>{{cite web|work=The Irish Times|title=Dramatist Harris wins Rooney Prize|url=http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/breaking/2012/1002/breaking55.html|date=10 October 2012}}</ref> * 2013: Ciarán Collins * 2014: Colin Barrett * 2015: [[Sara Baume]] * 2016: [[Doireann Ní Ghríofa]]<ref>{{cite web|work=The Irish Times|title=Poet Doireann Ní Ghríofa awarded €10,000 Rooney Prize for Irish Literature 2016|url=http://www.irishtimes.com/culture/books/poet-doireann-n%C3%AD-ghr%C3%ADofa-awarded-10-000-rooney-prize-for-irish-literature-2016-1.2780211|date=5 September 2016|accessdate=5 September 2016}}</ref> * 2017: Elizabeth Reapy * 2018: Caitriona Lally<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.post-gazette.com/ae/books/2018/10/03/A-Dublin-janitor-wins-the-Rooney-Prize-for-Irish-Literature-from-the-university-she-cleans/stories/201810030199|title=A Dublin janitor wins the Rooney Prize for Irish Literature from the university she cleans|work=Pittsburgh Post-Gazette|access-date=2018-10-12|language=en}}</ref>
